I disagree with this.  You state that the person with the gun caused it because if he doesn't pull the trigger, then the action does not happen.  However, if the people in the van don't floor the accelerator and try to run a roadblock when they see soldiers with guns there (and perhaps try to kill some americans, we'll never really know most likely), then the action doesn't happen.  Both are causal.  In my opinion, the chain you speak of goes all the way back past us being there to Saddam refusing to disarm and comply with the UN.  However, where you draw that line is clearly a matter of opinion.<br>
